text:
Let that day be dark;
    let God above not care about it;
        let no light shine over it.

Let darkness and deep gloom reclaim it;
    let clouds settle down on it;
        let blackness in mid-day terrify it.

Let darkness carry that night away;
    let it not take its place joyfully among the days of the year;
        let it not be entered into the calendar.

Let the stars of its evening twilight be dark;
    let it hope for light but let there be none;
        let it not see the breaking rays of the dawn.

I will not be at ease;
    I will not be quiet;
I will not rest;
    because trouble has arrived.”

“The lioness may roar,
    and the lion cub may growl;
        but even the ivory teeth of the full grown lion are broken.

His children are far from deliverance;
    they’ll be maltreated before they leave home,
        with no one to rescue them.

“Look! We have thought all this through,
    and what we’ve said is true;
        So please listen and learn for your own good!”

“The arrows of the Almighty have pierced me;
    my spirit absorbs their poison;
        God’s terrors have been arranged just for me!

The eyes of the one who sees me won’t see me anymore;
    your eyes will look for me
        but I won’t be around!

“In addition, I won’t keep my opinion to myself;
    I’ll speak from my distressed spirit;
        I’ll complain with my bitter soul.

if you are clean and upright,
    surely then, he’ll act on your behalf
        and restore your rightful place.

“I’m blameless;
    I don’t know myself;
        I despise my life.

A land is given into the hands of a wicked person;
    he covers the faces of its judges.
        If it is not God, then who is it?”

It’s a gloomy land, like deepest darkness;
    where there’s no order,
        and where even the brightness is like darkness.’”

But what the wicked look for will fail;
    their way of escape will be taken away from them;
        their only hope is to take their final breath.”

Like you, I also have understanding.
    I’m not inferior to you;
        who doesn’t know things like this?”

You’ve locked my feet in stocks;
    you watch all my steps;
        You’ve limited where I can walk.

so also a person lies down and does not get up;
    they won’t awaken until the heavens are no more,
        nor will they arise from their sleep.”

Water wears away stones;
    floods wash away topsoil from the land—
        but you destroy the hope of human beings just like that!

He won’t escape darkness;
    a flame will wither his shoots;
        and he’ll depart by the breath of God’s mouth.

His anger tears me in his persistent resentment against me;
    he gnashes his teeth at me.
        My adversary glares at me.

People gaped at me with mouths wide open;
    they slap me in their scorn
        and gather together against me.

“He tore me apart when I was at ease;
    grabbing me by my neck, he shook me to pieces—
        then he really made me his target.

His archers surround me,
    slashing open my kidneys without pity;
        he pours out my gall on the ground.

“My spirit is crushed,
    my days are over;
        it’s the grave for me!

My days are passed;
    my plans have been shattered;
        along with my heart’s desires.

He blocked my path,
    so I cannot pass;
        and he turned out the lights on my pathways.

He is breaking me down on every side,
    and now it’s too late for me;
        he has uprooted my hopes like a tree.

His troops march in a column against me,
    erecting their siege ramps against me;
        they surround my tent.”

Make sure that you remain wary of God’s sword,
    for God’s wrath brings with it the sword of punishment,
        by which you’ll know there’s a judgment.”

“He will restore what he has attained from his work
    and won’t consume it;
        he won’t enjoy the profits from his business transactions,

It will impale him and come out through his back;
    the point will glisten as it protrudes through his gall bladder,
        and he will be terrified.

“Total darkness has been reserved for his treasures;
    a fire that has no need to be kindled will devour him
        and consume whatever remains in his possession.

May they become like a straw,
    blown away before the wind;
        like a chaff that’s swept off by a storm.

The runoff from the streams will seem sweet to him;
    everyone will follow after him;
        countless crows march ahead of him.

“For when they’re humbled, you may respond;
    ‘It’s their pride!’
        but he delivers the humble.

“Then there are those who rebel against the light;
    they are not acquainted with its ways;
        and they don’t stay on its course.

They break into houses in the dark;
    during the day they remained sealed in.
        They don’t know daylight.

“They remain only a short time on the water’s surface;
    their inheritance will be cursed in the land;
        no one will work in their vineyards.

They’re exalted momentarily, but then they are gone;
    they are humbled, just like all the others.
        They are cut down like heads of corn.

He has commanded mankind:
    ‘To fear the Lord—that is wisdom;
        to move away from evil—that is understanding.’”

I set an example of the way to live, as a leader would;
    I lived like a king among his army;
        like one who comforts mourners.”

“A wretched crowd ambushes me to my right;
    they trip my feet;
        they build up their path of calamity for me.

They tear up my pathways;
    they profit from my destruction,
        and they need no help to do this!

My greatest fears have overcome me;
    my honor is assaulted as though by a wind storm;
        my prosperity evaporates like a morning cloud.”

(even a poor man had grown up with me as if I were his father,
    and even though I had guided the widow
        from the time I was born),

Shall I continue to wait, since they’re no longer talking?
    After all, they’re only standing there;
        they’re no longer responding.

since I don’t know the first thing about how to flatter;
    and the one who made me would sweep me away
        as if I were nothing.”

Let him pray to God
    and he will accept him;
        he will appear before him with joyful shouts!”

because he repays a person for his behavior;
    and according to a person’s conduct,
        he lets it happen to him.

“They die suddenly, in the middle of the night;
    people suffer seizures and pass away;
even valiant men can be taken away—
    and not by human hands.

because he has been adding rebellion to his sin;
    he claps his hands among us,
        and keeps on ranting against God.”

Theirs is a useless plea—
    God won’t listen;
        the Almighty won’t pay any attention.

He won’t stop looking at righteous people;
    he seats them on thrones with kings forever,
        and they are exalted.

“Now I’ll conclude with this:
    my heart is trembling violently;
        it feels like it’s about to leap from my body!

His thunder roars after it;
    his majestic voice will thunder;
and no one can trace them
    once his voice has been heard.

Their young are strong;
    they grow up in the open field;
then they go off
    and don’t return to them.”

He paws the ground in the valley
    and rejoices in his strength;
        he goes out to face weapons.

He scoffs at fear
    and is never scared;
        he never retreats from a sword.

“Beneath him he is armored as with sharp potsherds;
    he tears through muddy ground
        like a threshing sledge through grain.
